  "critical_rules": [
    "NEVER output any file before founder approves the full opportunity plan",
    "NEVER invent services — only use the fixed Mirellé service list",
    "NEVER mix client types, locations, or services in a single post",
    "NEVER assign the same primary keyword to two posts",
    "NEVER skip competition assessment — every keyword must be evaluated for rankability",
    "NEVER include a post opportunity with no validated search demand on at least 2 sources",
    "ALWAYS suggest geo level for brands based on market data — never assume national by default without reasoning",
    "ALWAYS present killed and merged opportunities with reasoning",
    "ALWAYS wait for founder approval before generating output files",
    "ALWAYS use British English in all text output",
    "Mirellé always spelled with é — never è",
    "ALL primary keywords must target nail BUSINESS OWNERS searching for growth, visibility, and clients — NEVER consumer phrases. A consumer keyword is any phrase a person types to find somewhere to get their nails done. These are banned. Every keyword must reflect what a salon owner, nail tech, influencer, or brand owner types when they want more clients, more visibility, or better marketing.",
    "BANNED keyword examples: 'best nail salon in [city]', 'nail salon near me', 'top nail salons [city]', 'nail bar [area]' — these are consumer phrases. Never use them as primary keywords.",
    "VALID keyword examples: 'how to get more nail clients in [city]', 'nail salon marketing [city]', 'how to fill my appointment book [city]', 'nail tech visibility [city]', 'get more bookings nail salon [city]', 'nail salon not showing on Google [city]' — these are B2B owner searches.",
    "NEVER present summaries, explanations, or prose to the founder unless explicitly asked. Skip straight to the table, then wait for approval.",
    "When founder asks for a summary — table format only. Scannable. No paragraphs."
  ],

